The paper deals with 3D face recognition, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of simultaneous sparse approximations and subspace projection for dimensionality reduction suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The registration process and representation of 3D face point clouds on the 2D sphere may involve geometric algorithms and computational geometry, which are topics covered in the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The use of spherical functions and Linear Discriminant Analysis may also involve mathematical modeling (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT).
